{"id": 225012818, "title": "PS5 Slim price cut again as PlayStation VR2 receives huge discount", "text": "Save \u00a340 on a PS5 Slim (Sony Interactive Entertainment) Sony has once again given the PS5 Slim console a temporary price cut, along with the PSVR2 and a number of games in the Days Of Play sale. As part of Sony\u2019s Days Of Play promotion, the company has announced widespread discounts across PlayStation hardware. The annual sale event is now live around the world and covers a huge assortment of games and PlayStation consoles. While it isn\u2019t as generous as previous discounts, the price of the PS5 Slim console (with a disc drive) is now \u00a3439.99, a \u00a340 reduction from \u00a3479.99. The digital version, meanwhile, has also dropped by \u00a340 to \u00a3349.99. This discount is available from PlayStation Direct, but it also reflected by other online retailers like Amazon, Currys, and Argos at the same price. If you\u2019ve been on the fence about picking up a PlayStation VR2, now might be the best time to consider it. The headset by itself has been reduced by \u00a390 from \u00a3529.99 to \u00a3439.99, while a bundle with Horizon Call Of The Mountain is now available for \u00a3479.99. This promotion is only for a limited time, with all the discounts set to end on Wednesday June 12, or while stocks last. As for the discounted games available digitally on the PlayStation Store, the highlights include 25% off Marvel\u2019s Spider-Man 2 and Final Fantasy 7 Rebirth. Star Wars Jedi: Survivor has also been knocked down by 55%. You can check out the full list of games here. More TrendingCall Of Duty fans 'insulted' by \u00a3700 bundle ahead of Game Pass inclusionFIFA 2K25 out this year as Take-Two gains licence claims retailerLego Zelda Great Deku Tree set interview - \u2018This is a very important model to all of us\u2019Doom: The Dark Ages is next game from id Software and will be on PS5 claim sourcesRead More Stories While Sony was expected to stage a PlayStation event of some kind in May, at time of writing the company has yet to announce anything. Some have speculated there may have been confusion among insiders with a corporate strategy meeting within Sony, which took place last week, but with only two days of May left it won\u2019t be long till we know one way or the other. There is, however, an event planned for the Silent Hill 2 remake on Thursday, which might suggest Sony is waiting until Summer Game Fest next month to make any minor announcements it might have. The PlayStation VR2 marked the dawn of a new Horizon (Sony Interactive Entertainment) Email gamecentral@metro.co.uk, leave a comment below, follow us on Twitter, and sign-up to our newsletter. To submit Inbox letters and Reader\u2019s Features more easily, without the need to send an email, just use our Submit Stuff page here. For more stories like this, check our Gaming page. MORE : Doom: The Dark Ages is next game from id Software and will be on PS5 claim sources MORE : Half of all PlayStation players still don\u2019t have a PS5 MORE : Sony finally hints at PS5 PlayStation Showcase this month Sign up to all the exclusive gaming content, latest releases before they're seen on the site.Sign upPrivacy Policy \u00bbThis site is protected by reCAPTCHA and the Google Privacy Policy and Terms of Service apply.", "summary": "Sony has once again given the PS5 Slim console a temporary price cut, along with the PSVR2 and a number of games in the Days Of Play sale.", "url": "https://metro.co.uk/2024/05/29/ps5-slim-price-cut-playstation-vr2-receives-huge-discount-20931350/", "image": "https://metro.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/SEI_206565287-94f2.jpg?quality=90&strip=all", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-29 12:17:52", "author": "Adam Starkey", "authors": ["Adam Starkey"], "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": 0.013}